task.summary: Default task
Scaffolding project. npm installed Express and EJS. node server/main.js to launch
Gulp files. LiveServer and BrowserSync.
Bower install React. NPM install React. Built JSX file
Browserify Reactify workflow. Also vinyl-source-stream
minor edit

Added GroceryItemList.jsx component. Currently the app is: 1) taking our jsx 2) browserifying it 3) reactifying it to JS 4) moving it temp 5) then our index.ejs is being compiled on the fly to html and reading the JS file in .tmp dir
Built array of items rendering them .jsx
Created GroceryItem.jsx
Implemented a functioning dispatcher. Made a className with a ternary operator for stying items that have been purchased
Added GroceryListAddItem button and input
Created three new methods to the GroceryListAddItems.jsx. Currently working in the console.
Created GroceryItemActionCreator.jsx that requires the dispatcher and dispatches the input field payload on submit
Created a 'Store' which contains a ES5 class that handles items submitted
Moved Items into GroceryItemStore.jsx and chaned main.jsx to re-render page on item submit.
Added delete item functionality
Added buy and unbuy methods. Working in Chrome
Added skeleton style sheets for simplistic styling
Added routes folder and moved static array of items into items.js
Stopping tutorial at the end of the React lesson. NOT doing the express portion.
Added more items to the db.
Added additional inputs that are loading to the view
Added: gulp-babel, gulp-traceur, gulp-typescript, gulp-plumber, gulp-concat, gulp-uglify (http://weblogs.asp.net/dwahlin/getting-started-with-es6-%E2%80%93-transpiling-es6-to-es5)
Finished set up for tracuer and babel feeding into a dist folder
